The article discusses the importance of Transgender Day of Visibility in honoring and celebrating the achievements and resilience of transgender individuals and communities. It acknowledges the progress made in advancing civil rights for transgender and gender non-binary people, but also highlights the systemic barriers and discrimination they still face. The Biden-Harris Administration is committed to stamping out discrimination and protecting the civil rights of transgender Americans, as evidenced by the Executive Order signed on the first day in office. The article calls for the passage of the Equality Act to provide federal civil rights protections for LGBTQ+ Americans. It concludes by affirming the worth and dignity of transgender individuals and urging all Americans to join in the fight for full equality.